This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses image analysis methodologies and introduces a new logical language for querying images. It also mentions two examples of analysis of Magnetic Resonance images, which is a common application of computer vision in medical imaging. 

The paper also involves the use of statistical similarity operators, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of state-of-the-art algorithms for efficient implementation of distance-based operators suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper discusses the use of topological spaces and closure spaces, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
